{
  "name": "Elite Intellect",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/fleur-de-lis-yellow.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Skill</p><p>Prerequisite: Intelligence 20, Level 10+</p><p>You have the cunning of the most prolific scholars, granting the following benefits:</p><p>• You gain a 1d4 bonus to all Intelligence saving throws you make.</p><p>• You gain Mastery in one Intelligence Skill which you already have proficiency in.</p><p>• Intelligence ability and skill checks you make ignore any penalty inflicted by a creature or effect</p><p>• You reduce the Downtime cost required to complete any training to the following; </p><p>- 1 Week: New Tool or Vehicle Proficiency.</p><p>- 3 Weeks: New Weapon or Language Proficiency.</p><p>- 5 Weeks: New Armor Proficiency.</p><p>- 8 Weeks: New Skill Proficiency.</p><p>- 16 Weeks: New Feat.</p><p></p>",
